- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a family of distances on the set of discrete time series, which involves algorithmic and data structure considerations. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed distance is well-suited for processing event data, which is a common type of data in machine learning applications. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the proposed distance can be used for similarity search and clustering, which are common tasks in AI. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the proposed distance can be used for matching and aligning time series, which is a common task in computer vision. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes and proves some properties of the proposed distances, which can be related to information theory.
